{"title_page": "'Bout Love", "text_new": "{{for|the Plasticines album|About Love (album)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = 'Bout Love\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Bill Withers]]\n| cover      = Billwithers_boutlove.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1978\n| recorded   = 1978\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soul music|Soul]]\n| length     = 38:50\n| label      = [[Columbia Records]]\n| producer   = Paul Smith\n| prev_title = [[Menagerie (album)|Menagerie]]\n| prev_year  = 1977\n| next_title = Watching You Watching Me\n| next_year  = 1985\n}}\n\n''''''Bout Love''''' is the seventh studio album by [[United States|American]] [[R&B]] singer [[Bill Withers]], released in 1978 on the [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] label.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1     =[[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic |class=album |id=r22129 |tab=review |label=Bill Withers: '''Bout Love'' - Review |first=Ed  |last=Hogan |accessdate=August 29, 2011}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|Christgau's Record Guide]]''\n| rev3Score = C<ref name=\"CG\">{{cite book|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|year=1981|title=[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies]]|publisher=[[Ticknor & Fields]]|isbn=089919026X|chapter=Consumer Guide '70s: W|chapter-url=https://www.robertchristgau.com/get_chap.php?k=W&bk=70|accessdate=March 22, 2019|via=robertchristgau.com}}</ref>\n}}\n\nBill Withers collaborated with [[Paul Smith (pianist)|Paul Smith]] on '' 'Bout Love'', who co-wrote all but \"Memories Are That Way\" with Withers. '''Bout Love'' features Withers' usual mellowness and introspective lyrics, however its lead single, \"Don't It Make It Better\" is up-tempo, and its follow-up single, \"You Got the Stuff\" is a [[funk]] song. \"Don't It Make It Better\" peaked at No. 30 on [[Billboard R&B Singles]], but \"You Got the Stuff\" reached only No. 85 on the chart.<ref name=Love>{{cite web|title=\"'Bout Love\"  Charts & Awards|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=March 14, 2010|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/bout-love-r22129/charts-awards}}</ref>\n\n'' 'Bout Love'' peaked at #50 on the [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|R&B chart]] and No. 134 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. It was re-released as a digital music download in 2008.<ref name=Amazon>{{cite web|title=Amazon.com: 'Bout Love|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=January 17, 2013|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002GKEC0G/}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n# \"All Because Of You\" <small>(Bill Withers, [[Paul Smith (pianist)|Paul Smith]])</small> \u2013 3:50\n# \"Dedicated To You My Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:47\n# \"Don't It Make It Better\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:12\n# \"You Got The Stuff\" <small>(Withers, Smith, Keith Hatchell)</small> \u2013 7:14\n# \"Look To Each Other For Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:23\n# \"Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:57\n# \"Love Is\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:21\n# \"Memories Are That Way\" <small>(Withers)</small> \u2013 5:06\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Bill Withers&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, guitar (A1, A3, A4, B3, B4), bass (A1), whistle (A2), acoustic piano (A4), drums (B4)\n* Paul Smith&nbsp;\u2013 keyboards, synthesizer\n* [[Jeff Paris (musician)|Geoffrey Leib]]- keyboards (B4)\n* Clifford Coulter- synthesizer (B4)\n* [[Wah Wah Watson]]- electric guitar (A1)\n* Bryan Garofalo&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* [[Keni Burke]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* [[Jerry Knight]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* Keith Hatchell- bass (A4)\n* [[Russ Kunkel]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* [[Harvey Mason]]- drums (A4)\n* [[Ralph MacDonald]]&nbsp;\u2013 percussion\n* [[Buddy Collette]]- flute solo (A2)\n<ref>Bill Withers - ''Bout Love'' liner notes.</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1979)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Pop Albums]]<ref name=\"allmusic albums\">{{Cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p5859/charts-awards/billboard-albums|pure_url=yes}}|title=Bill Withers US albums chart history|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref>\n| align=center|134\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|Top Soul Albums]]<ref name=\"allmusic albums\" />\n| align=center|50\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Single\n! colspan=\"3\"| Chart positions<ref name=\"allmusic singles\">{{Cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p5859/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}}|title=Bill Withers US singles chart history|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref>\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! width=\"40\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US<br>R&B]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1979\n| align=\"left\"| \"Don't It Make It Better \"\n| 30\n|-\n| align=\"left\"| \"You Got The Stuff \"\n| 85\n|-\n|}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.discogs.com/Bill-Withers-Bout-Love/master/255718 Bill Withers-'Bout Love at Discogs]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Bill Withers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bout Love}}\n[[Category:1978 albums]]\n[[Category:Bill Withers albums]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Paul Smith (pianist)]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the Plasticines album|About Love (album)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = 'Bout Love\n| type       = Studio\n| artist     = [[Bill Withers]]\n| cover      = Billwithers_boutlove.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 1978\n| recorded   = 1978\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soul music|Soul]]\n| length     = 38:50\n| label      = [[Columbia Records]]\n| producer   = Paul Smith\n| prev_title = [[Menagerie (album)|Menagerie]]\n| prev_year  = 1977\n| next_title = Watching You Watching Me\n| next_year  = 1985\n}}\n\n''''''Bout Love''''' is the seventh studio album by [[United States|American]] [[R&B]] singer [[Bill Withers]], released in 1978 on the [[Columbia Records|Columbia]] label.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1     =[[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic |class=album |id=r22129 |tab=review |label=Bill Withers: '''Bout Love'' - Review |first=Ed  |last=Hogan |accessdate=August 29, 2011}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|Christgau's Record Guide]]''\n| rev3Score = C<ref name=\"CG\">{{cite book|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|year=1981|title=[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies]]|publisher=[[Ticknor & Fields]]|isbn=089919026X|chapter=Consumer Guide '70s: W|chapter-url=https://www.robertchristgau.com/get_chap.php?k=W&bk=70|accessdate=March 22, 2019|via=robertchristgau.com}}</ref>\n}}\n\nBill Withers collaborated with [[Paul Smith (pianist)|Paul Smith]] on '' 'Bout Love'', who co-wrote all but \"Memories Are That Way\" with Withers. '''Bout Love'' features Withers's usual mellowness and introspective lyrics, however its lead single, \"Don't It Make It Better\" is up-tempo, and its follow-up single, \"You Got the Stuff\" is a [[funk]] song. \"Don't It Make It Better\" peaked at No. 30 on [[Billboard R&B Singles]], but \"You Got the Stuff\" reached only No. 85 on the chart.<ref name=Love>{{cite web|title=\"'Bout Love\"  Charts & Awards|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=March 14, 2010|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/bout-love-r22129/charts-awards}}</ref>\n\n'' 'Bout Love'' peaked at #50 on the [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|R&B chart]] and No. 134 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]. It was re-released as a digital music download in 2008.<ref name=Amazon>{{cite web|title=Amazon.com: 'Bout Love|publisher=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=January 17, 2013|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B002GKEC0G/}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n# \"All Because Of You\" <small>(Bill Withers, [[Paul Smith (pianist)|Paul Smith]])</small> \u2013 3:50\n# \"Dedicated To You My Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:47\n# \"Don't It Make It Better\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:12\n# \"You Got The Stuff\" <small>(Withers, Smith, Keith Hatchell)</small> \u2013 7:14\n# \"Look To Each Other For Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:23\n# \"Love\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:57\n# \"Love Is\" <small>(Withers, Smith)</small> \u2013 4:21\n# \"Memories Are That Way\" <small>(Withers)</small> \u2013 5:06\n\n== Personnel ==\n* Bill Withers&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, guitar (A1, A3, A4, B3, B4), bass (A1), whistle (A2), acoustic piano (A4), drums (B4)\n* Paul Smith&nbsp;\u2013 keyboards, synthesizer\n* [[Jeff Paris (musician)|Geoffrey Leib]]- keyboards (B4)\n* Clifford Coulter- synthesizer (B4)\n* [[Wah Wah Watson]]- electric guitar (A1)\n* Bryan Garofalo&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* [[Keni Burke]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* [[Jerry Knight]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass\n* Keith Hatchell- bass (A4)\n* [[Russ Kunkel]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums\n* [[Harvey Mason]]- drums (A4)\n* [[Ralph MacDonald]]&nbsp;\u2013 percussion\n* [[Buddy Collette]]- flute solo (A2)\n<ref>Bill Withers - ''Bout Love'' liner notes.</ref>\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Chart (1979)\n! Peak<br>position\n|-\n| [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Pop Albums]]<ref name=\"allmusic albums\">{{Cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p5859/charts-awards/billboard-albums|pure_url=yes}}|title=Bill Withers US albums chart history|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref>\n| align=center|134\n|-\n| ''Billboard'' [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|Top Soul Albums]]<ref name=\"allmusic albums\" />\n| align=center|50\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Single\n! colspan=\"3\"| Chart positions<ref name=\"allmusic singles\">{{Cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p5859/charts-awards/billboard-singles|pure_url=yes}}|title=Bill Withers US singles chart history|publisher=allmusic.com|accessdate=2011-08-29}}</ref>\n|- style=\"font